        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-05 22:33:56.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 llite: complete IT_WRITE_LEASE implementation",
        "message": "LU-0000 llite: complete IT_WRITE_LEASE implementation\n\nComplete the IT_WRITE_LEASE intent implementation by adding\nmissing support in core Lustre infrastructure functions.\n\nThis patch adds IT_WRITE_LEASE support in it_to_lock_mode()\nreturning LCK_EX, IT_WRITE_LEASE string representation in\nldlm_it2str(), and client-side write lease acquisition in\nll_file_io_generic().\n\nThe IT_WRITE_LEASE intent now works end-to-end, allowing\nclients to acquire exclusive write lease locks during write\noperations. This provides the foundation for concurrent write\nfunctionality in mirrored files.\n\nTesting shows the implementation works without kernel crashes\nand properly acquires/releases write lease locks during file\nwrite operations.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I2af282930751c4395895f5af2c5837e5d52f63bc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
